post_text:
What a crazy ending to a wonderful school year. The Texas Education Agency continues to work on plans for re-opening school in the fall.
Please rest assured that Treetops will offer learning opportunities for all of our students that you as parents will be comfortable with. Treetops is looking into options for all parents and students in a blended learning capacity to help facilitate safety for all of our families. Take a few weeks to just enjoy your children and the beginning of summer. Updates as to what our school will look like will be posted once the Texas Education Agency works out all the kinks. Treetops is a magical place because of our families and faculty. Watch our website and Facebook page for updates. Have a safe summer.
Ms. Lou

Can you figure out whose Bitmoji is whose? Treetops teachers and staff have all supplied their own personal Bitmojis that are shown in the following photos. Make a numbered list (1-37) and take your best guesses and email Ms. Laura at lauragreenlee@treetops.org. The yearbook link will be posted at treetops.org later today. Take a look at staff pictures on pages 62-63 to give you a little help.

We will have 2 small prizes for students and their families that guess the most correctly. If more than one family gets the most correct guesses, we'll draw randomly from those "ties" to see who will receive the prizes.

Guesses are due by Thursday, May 21 at noon. I'll announce the winners Friday morning.

post_text:
Hello Mrs. Andrea,
I don‚Äôt even know where to begin. Thank you for putting this assignment together. These letters are the most sweetest and heartfelt, cutest letters I have ever read in my life. I am usually so strong, but as I began to read, my eyes filled up with tears and my heart was full of compassion. I had to stop reading them or continue to read the letters and go home for the rest of day.
My heart says Thank you to all of the children that took out time, to write and ask questions. We will get these printed out for the residents.

Continual Prayers, Tosha Sadler and La DoraJ

We will surely meet again
I don't know where and I don't know when
I hope we have a lot of sunny days
And the sun will shine in a funny way

Everyone is waiting for this to get better
But time is fading
And my pillow's getting wetter from my tears
And we are all at home

Feeling alone
Take me back

When school was my home

By Derren Klander DeLeon
Treetops School International Student

post_text:
The world is grappling with an issue of enormous scale and human impact, and our hearts go out to all who have been affected by the outbreak of coronavirus (COVID-19).
At Treetops it is our responsibility to prioritize the health and well-being of our families while also playing a constructive role in supporting local health officials and government leaders as they work to contain the virus. We will continue to make decisions with vigilance and courage informed by the latest CDC information, Tarrant County Health Department and in consultation with the Texas Education Agency.
I am in conversation to implement measures consistent with other schools to keep everyone safe. The buildings have been sanitized and information will be forthcoming this week and we will share with our community via our website and social media.
Ms. Lou

post_text:
On behalf of all of our homeless pets and Trinity GAP volunteers, we want to send a heartfelt thank you for the amazingly generous Amazon gift card and cash donations. We have so many dogs in need and this is going to make a huge difference to our ability to help meet their medical needs.

We also want to thank you for doing such a great job on educating our youth about the importance of homeless pets and responsible pet ownership.

God bless and thank you again,

Steffenie Vela
President, Trinity GAP Rescue

post_text:
Why does Treetops participate in community service?

It is the opportunity to build a Culture of Kindness With a Day of Service from Kindergarten to Seniors.

When Treetops students spend a day focusing on helping others, they see their own capacity to make a difference in their community.

The students love this day, and there's a great sense of pride.

Every single student understands how easy it is to provide those services to a multitude of organizations within this area.

We owe our students that commitment to help them realize what they can do to be well-rounded citizens.

Just another example of what makes Treetops a special place.

Ms. Lou
